==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|halou}}, {{m|enm|halow}}, {{m|enm|halloo||pos=interjection used to call attention}}, representing {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hēlā}}, {{m|ang|ǣlā}}, {{m|ang|ēalā||O!, alas!, oh!, lo!}}, equivalent to {{compound|hey|lo|lang=en}}.

===Interjection===
{{en-interj}}

# {{alt form|hello|lang=en}}
# {{lb|en|dated}} A cry of [[surprise]].
#* '''1890''', [[w:Sir Arthur Conan Doyle|Sir Arthur Conan Doyle]], ''[[s:The Sign of the Four|The Sign of the Four]]'',
#*: It sounds like a sum in the rule of three. The answer should give us the — But '''hallo'''! here are the accredited representatives of the law.

